A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Georgia's working women for their contributions toward
2 building strong families and supporting the Georgia Economy; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Georgia strives to remain the number one state to do business, and economic
4 security is an important concern for women, their children, their partners, and for the health
5 of Georgia's communities and economy; and
6 WHEREAS, women comprise more than half of Georgia's adult population and are the
7 primary or co-breadwinners in more than half of all Georgia households with children,
8 making up over 65 percent of the low-wage, essential worker workforce; and
9 WHEREAS, research has shown that policy solutions such as salary transparency, increased
10 paid sick days and paid leave, accessible and affordable childcare, stable housing and
11 workplace protections have a positive impact on women and families, and would boast the
12 Georgia economy by as much as $4.4 billion; and
13 WHEREAS, access to healthy foods, clean air and water, public transportation, affordable
14 and safe housing, and equitable utility services are all integral to a working woman and her
15 family's health and financial stability; and
