16 WHEREAS, protections for pregnant women at work ensures that women remain an integral
17 part of the workforce, have healthy pregnancies and deliveries, and strengthens Georgia
18 families; and
19 WHEREAS, Georgia currently has the third highest uninsured rate in the country, affordable
20 and accessible healthcare equates to a stronger and healthier workforce; and
21 WHEREAS, 60 percent of all Georgians cannot access the unpaid Family Medical Leave Act
22 due to eligibility or being unable to afford to take leave without pay; implementing policies
23 such as paid leave increases women's labor force participation rate.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
25 support legislation that would provide the economic support and security that women, their
26 families, and the Georgia economy need.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
28 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the public and the
29 press.
